====Verb====
{{en-verb}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To search, forage, or fish for yabbies.
#* {{quote-book|1=en|year=2005|editor=Mathews, F.|title=Reinhabiting Reality: Towards a Recovery of Culture|page=156|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qFNTk7_qRyAC&pg=PA156|text=He would have known the Merri well, given the affinity between boys and creeks, and he probably fished and '''yabbied''' there.}}
#* {{quote-book|1=en|year=2006|editor=Cowlishaw, G.|title=Bourke: Our Yarns: The Stories Behind 'Blackfellas, Whitefellas'|page=83|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eLoDEAAAQBAJ&pg=PA83|text=The kids in town now that have the most fun are the so-called 'feral kids'. They spend the whole days doing what we used to do, '''yabbying''' and on the river.}}
#* {{quote-book|1=en|year=2019|author=Zagar, C.|title=Your Feet Take You To Where Your Heart Is|page=90|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Uki_DwAAQBAJ&pg=PA90|text="Can we go '''yabbying'''?" "It'll be too hot," I say. "It's never too hot for '''yabbying'''." We are creating Christmas memories for our son.}}
=====Usage notes=====
Often used phrasally (''go yabbying''), by analogy with ''go fishing''.
===Etymology 2===
Unknown.
====Verb====
{{en-verb}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|Nigeria|slang}} To show disrespect by denouncing or insulting; to [[diss]].
#* {{quote-book|1=en|year=2019|author=Collins, J.|title=Fela: Katakuta Notes|page=160|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CmBcCAAAQBAJ&pg=PA160|text=So Abiola invite Fela to his house for a big party, and Fela have to go as they are family—even though Fela had '''yabbied''' Abiola in his song "ITT" [International Thief Thief]. And it's true, Abiola duped the country for that money—everybody knows it.}}
